# ── Worktree cache symlinks ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The worktree-setup skill symlinks cache/build directories in a new worktree
# back to the primary checkout for warm builds (e.g. `target -> /path/to/main
# checkout/target`). Directory-only gitignore patterns (trailing `/`) do NOT
# match a symlink of the same name, so every such symlink needs an explicit
# bare (no-trailing-slash) entry here, or `git add -A` silently tracks it —
# which then breaks CI on a fresh checkout (the tracked symlink resolves to a
# path that doesn't exist there, or collides with the directory a build tool
# expects to create). Keep this list in sync with what worktree-setup links.
apps/android/.gradle
apps/android/app/build
apps/android/build
apps/chrome-extension/dist
apps/palette-tauri/dist
apps/palette-tauri/node_modules
apps/palette-tauri/src-tauri/target
apps/web/.next
apps/web/node_modules
apps/web/out
scripts/.ruff_cache
src/vector/ops/commands/ask/context/build
docker/mem0/config.json
.superpowers/
/data/
http-cacache/
/storage/
.pnpm-store*
specs/.current-spec
**/.progress.md

